          <div class="pricing-card__range">$200 – $600+</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__note">Restaurant priority · True / Turbo Air · OEM parts</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-card__appliance">Washer / Dryer (incl. stackable)</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__range">$150 – $350</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__note">In-unit · OE drain · Thermal fuse · Compact space</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-card__appliance">Dishwasher</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__range">$150 – $320</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__note">LADWP scale · E24 · Galvanized pipe · Filter</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-card__appliance">Oven / Range</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__range">$150 – $400</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__note">Gas igniter · Bake element · Temperature calibration</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-card__appliance">Diagnostic Fee</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__range">$89</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__note">Waived with repair · Written report included</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="kt-faq">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Questions Koreatown Customers Ask</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Do you offer same-day appliance repair in Koreatown, LA?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. Our technicians cover all of Koreatown — Wilshire Blvd, Vermont Ave, 6th Street, Western Ave, and every residential and commercial address in 90005 and 90006. Call before noon for same-day afternoon service.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Do you repair appliances in Koreatown apartments and high-rise buildings?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. We're experienced with in-unit stackable units, compact galley kitchens, and building access coordination. We also provide written diagnostic reports for tenants to share with property managers.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Do you repair commercial refrigerators and restaurant equipment in Koreatown?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. We service commercial reach-in coolers and refrigeration units in restaurant settings throughout the Koreatown corridor. Call with your equipment brand and symptoms for same-day availability.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Can you provide a written diagnostic report for my landlord in Koreatown?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. We provide written diagnostic documentation as standard — brand, model, failure cause, repair description, and cost breakdown. Ready to forward to your building management or landlord.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Are you available on weekends in Koreatown?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. Saturday 8am–7pm and Sunday 9am–5pm.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is your diagnostic fee in Koreatown?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Our diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed with the repair. Written estimate before we start. Most Koreatown residential repairs run $150–$400.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Do you also serve Mid-Wilshire, Hancock Park, and Silver Lake?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. Our Koreatown service extends to Mid-Wilshire, Hancock Park, Hollywood, Echo Park, Silver Lake, West Hollywood, and all of central Los Angeles.</div></details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

